snippet.textDisplay: Consider that Intel still needs to deal with Spectre and Meltdown.......... AND they are still having trouble getting to 10nm.  And they are still trying to enter the market for discrete graphics cards, which probably isn't a good move, depending on what kind of customer they are targeting......... things are just piling up for Intel.  Considering all they have to deal with, considering the competition from nVidia and AMD, and considering that (so far), they seem like they can only respond by lowering prices.............. i am betting we would probably see executives stepping down, and layoffs, and some re-structuring happening if they can't get their act together by the end of 2020 at the very latest.
